properties.areaDesc: San Luis Obispo County Central Coast; Santa Barbara County Central Coast
properties.headline: High Surf Advisory issued February 1 at 1:27AM PST until February 3 at 10:00PM PST by NWS Los Angeles/Oxnard CA
properties.description:
* WHAT...Large breaking waves of 10 to 16 feet with local sets to
18 feet with dangerous rip currents. Peak surf is expected from
Sunday night through early Monday morning.

* WHERE...West-facing beaches of the Central Coast.

* WHEN...From 6 AM Sunday to 10 PM PST Monday.

* IMPACTS...There is an increased risk for ocean drowning. Rip
currents can pull swimmers and surfers out to sea. Large
breaking waves can cause injury, wash people off beaches and
rocks, and capsize small boats near shore.
properties.instruction:
Remain out of the water due to dangerous surf conditions, or stay
near occupied lifeguard towers. Rock jetties can be deadly in
such conditions, stay off the rocks.

NWSheadline: HIGH SURF ADVISORY IN EFFECT FROM 6 AM SUNDAY TO 10 PM PST MONDAY
